“Its all one blood, don't care about your face
The color of your eye
Or the tone of your skin
Don't care where you are
Don't care where you been
'Cause where we gonna go
Is where we wanna be
The place where the little language is unity..”
❤️💙💚
Song - One Tribe by The Black Eyed Peas

node.text: Garrett's PROUD DAD DANCE at the end of this video hah! We're stoked to be visiting @snowbird next week! These ski adventures have become a yearly tradition. node.text: At the end of the day we will offload our cameras to organize and watch our footage. It’s always such a fun joy seeing what special moments we missed that the cameras captured. WE HAD NO IDEA this even happened to @manillagee. He literally picked himself up and jumped back on the horse (after emptying the sand from his trunks and meeting a friendly pup;) 😅🐶😍

node.text: FAMILY MOVIE NIGHT watching #YouvsWild on @netflixfamily! 🦁🐒🦁 We embarked on an at-home mission to watch the new interactive movie "Animals on the Loose"! Stream and play along now, only on @Netflix, and show us how you're watching with your family using #YouvsWild 🗺️

node.text: GIRLS TURN!! 😩😱😅 Once again, another example of a parent TRYING to put on a brave face for their child!! Can you hear what Dorothy says at the very end?? 😳

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by The Bucket List Family on July 12, 2021 tagging @garrettgee, @jessgee, @dorothygee, @manillagee, @thebucketlistfamily, @matetsivictoriafalls, and @caligee. May be an image of 5 people, people standing and outdoors.

node.text:
There are some ups AND downs to traveling right now : 1 of the downs is how tricky logistics have become due to Covid testing most every time we switch a country or destination. BUT the ups have far outweighed the downs! Perhaps the biggest up so far has been seeing just how much it means to the countries and lodges and tour companies to be open again. Most of our stops thus far we have been their 1st guests since reopening. They are thrilled and just so grateful to be open again. We love to travel because the positive effect it has on our kids and family..BUT so grateful when we can return the favor and be a source of some good to the places we visit as well.. 😌❤️🌎💚🥰
/// @matetsivictoriafalls

node.text: Do you see it in the background?? 🐘 I’m so grateful to be here, on safari, in the bush, seeing these magnificent animals in their wild habitat. We just arrived at the beautiful @matetsivictoriafalls in Zimbabwe 🇿🇼. You can see in our Instagram stories today that the moment our safari jeep left the camp to explore for animals Garrett says, “You’re in your happy place right now..” and right then I begin to cry.. 😭🥰😭

node.text: The famous Giraffe Manor!! When we were planning our Summer Semester on Safari it was impossible not to include this magical place. It feels like a real life fairy tale on Earth. Timeless architecture, friendly hosts, and of course GIRAFFES!! This is our 2nd time here. The kids have talked about it ever since our visit in 2018 when we came here to gather inspiration for the kids room in our home. We arrived and were greeted with a big friendly “Welcome back to your home away from home. It feels like you were just here.” AND IT DOES.. 🦒❤️🦒💙🦒💚🦒 @thesafaricollection

node.text: 🌍 AND SO THE JOURNEY BEGINS!! 1st a 15hr flight on @qatarairways from Seattle to Qatar. Then a 5hr flight from Qatar to Kenya. This 1st photo was right before take off. The 2nd photo is my prediction of how we’ll look after we land 22hrs+ layer! 😉😅😉 Nah, WE GOT THIS! I keep reminding myself that these kids are seasoned pros! For years we accomplished these looong travel days on whatever the cheapest tickets we could find. I’m proud of how far we’ve come and sooo grateful to be working with #qatarairways and showing off their new FULL FAMILY seating!!?!! For reals?!! They call it the Qsuite and it’s my new favorite way to travel. Will show you more of it in our Instagram stories today and our YouTube video tomorrow!! ❤️💙💚
